<h2>Corresponding gene name search</h2>
<p>
<FORM METHOD="POST" ACTION="gene_crspnd.cgi" ENCTYPE="multipart/form-data">
<table width=100%>
<tr>
  <td bgcolor=#eeee77 colspan=3>
    <input type="text" name="srch_id" size="30">
    <select name="ver">
    <option value="1" selected>build 1.0 -> 2.5</option>
    <option value="2">build 2.5 -> 1.0</option>
    </select>
    <input type="submit" value="SUBMIT">
    <input type="reset" value="RESET">
    <br>
    Or load the CDS name(s) by a text file <INPUT TYPE="file" NAME="srch_id_file">
    <br>
    <br>
    Enter the CDS name(s) by separating each CDS name with a space (not comma).<br>
    <br>
    e.g.<br>
    <table cellspacing="5">
    <tr><td>chr1.CM0088.10.nd</td><td>chr1.CM0088.10.r2.d</td><td>( build 1.0 -> 2.5 )</td><tr>
    <tr><td>LjSGA_049910.1</td><td>chr1.CM0001.730.r2.m</td><td>( build 1.0 -> 2.5 )</td><tr>
    <tr><td>chr4.CM0007.360.r2.m</td><td>chr1.CM0088.10.nd</td><td>( build 2.5 -> 1.0 )</tr>
    </table>
  </td>
</tr>
</table>
</FORM>

<p>
<h2>About <i>Lotus japonicus</i></h2>

<p>
<i>Lotus japonicus</i> (Japanese common name: Miyakogusa) is a typical
model legume. Here we report the first whole genome structure of the
legume, <i>L. japonicus,</i> its characteristic genome features, and a
variety of information and material resources that were developed
during this
study. <a href="http://wiki.kazusa.or.jp/Kazusa:PlantDB:miyakogusa"><i>(Read
more...)</i></a>
</p>

